Network.Commands

Class Increase

  • java.lang.Object
    • Network.Commands.Increase
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Command

    public class Increase
extends java.lang.Object
implements Command
    One of the commands that a Client can execute. An Increase Command is executed after a Player has reached 1000 experience points. After reaching 1000 experience points, they are given three Increases which they can use on any of the folowing options: Strength, Dexterity, Health, and Precision.
    Author:
    Matt Latura

    • Method Detail

      • execute

        public void execute(Server s,
           java.lang.String message,
           Server.ClientManager cm)
        Execute the Increase command. If the Player has available stat increases, check for a correct argument. If the argument is correct, increase the stat and alert the Player that it has been increased. If the argument is wrong, alert them what the possible options are. If the Player does not have available stat increases, alert them that they do not have enough and give them information on how to get them.
        Specified by:
        execute in interface Command
        Parameters:
        s - The server that the Command is associated with. The server is sent because it contains everything from the world and anything else that the method may need.
        message - The arguments that have been sent to this command. Not every command needs arguments, but many do. For example, if a client typed give iron sword Hero, the message argument would be iron sword Hero. The command should know how to parse these.
        cm - The ClientManager that has executed this command. ClientManagers hold players and can allow the server to communicate with the client directly from the command.
